                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="72214" author="luke" created="Wed, 2 Nov 2011 05:07:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The root cause of your stacktrace is a NullPointerException in your code. Could you please clarify why you think there is a bug in Spring Security and provide a self-contained test case project which demonstrates the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="72216" author="luke" created="Wed, 2 Nov 2011 06:14:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hmm. This could actually be the same issue as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1837&quot; title=&quot;Problem appear when add @PreAuthorize to a controller using @PathVariable&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1837&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1837&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. As in that issue, please try decoupling the infrastructure beans (such as your PermissionEvaluator) from the beans you are injecting into them, using a bean factory lookup instead, for example. Failing that, please provide a reproducible test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="74328" author="rwinch" created="Fri, 30 Dec 2011 16:17:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1813&quot; title=&quot;not able to fetch the queries from the property file using spring message source&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1813&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1813&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which contains a little better documentation on how to reproduce this issue (and reported by the same user), it appears that this is not a bug.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is that Spring does not know that there is a dependency from SecurityDao to SecuritySQLReader since SecurityDao attempts to assign SecurityDao.Query_SQL the result of SecuritySQLReader.getMessage(&quot;KeyString&quot;). This means Spring does not know that SecuritySQLReader needs the MessageSource wired before creating SecurityDao.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Ganesh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you disagree can you please provide a complete test case that demonstrates that this is an issue with Spring Security. Note the attachements on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-1813&quot; title=&quot;not able to fetch the queries from the property file using spring message source&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SEC-1813&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SEC-1813&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; do not compile, so I do not view that as a complete example test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="74333" author="rockgans" created="Sun, 1 Jan 2012 06:10:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Rob - Thanks for the detailed explanation. I will add a complete test case replicating the scenario. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76976" author="rwinch" created="Mon, 19 Mar 2012 07:48:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing since the code provided did not demonstrate any issues with Spring Security and no updates have been made&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="124760" author="issuemaster" created="Sat, 6 Feb 2016 06:18:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/2042&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-security/issues/2042&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
